  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      We aim to test the hypothesis that Laser speckle contrast imaging allows for the measurement
      of cutaneous blood flow during exercise.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Ischemia and post occlusive reactive hyperhemia in the skin is tested in healthy normal
      subjects at rest and during cycle exercise.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
